						<summary>

						<p>This is very probably an inscription of <hi rend="bold">Parāntaka I.</hi> It records a gift of 96 sheep left with the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Tirutturutti by the chief <hi rend="bold">Siddhavaḍavaṉ Gāmuṇḍaṉ of Milāḍu</hi> for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple with the daily supply of an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee.</p>						

						</summary>
